{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9cb6a10-a3a7-44e1-a454-b37a3e7cb7b2","content":"For a **web API project**, common templates and auth options depend on your stack:\n\n### .NET\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual    # Identity-based (JWT bearer)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg     # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg      # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows       # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n### Node.js\n- **Express** + Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, OpenID Connect)\n- **Fastify** + @fastify/jwt or @fastify/oauth2\n\n### Python\n- **FastAPI** + OAuth2/JWT (built-in security utilities)\n- **Django REST Framework** + TokenAuth, JWT, or SessionAuth\n\n### Common Auth Schemes\n| Scheme | Best For |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth 2.0 / OIDC** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **API Keys** | Server-to-server, simple integrations |\n| **Cookie/Session** | Traditional web apps |\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? Let me know your preferred stack and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6277fa73-f83d-47b4-9ce2-3e69dfb1b37a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":366,"requestId":"401D:913B3:421ED1:4D69DA:69F00420"},"id":"126e1f9f-9f38-4825-b4d5-af70933f46d1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:44.834Z","parentId":"98f2afe9-fe5f-41e8-b765-d4e269c0b167"}
